      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Looks a great contest between two last-start winners, both with upside, both have won here and both have good speed. TENNESSEE SPIRIT (4) is a little more seasoned but had her first run here last time with an all-the-way win. Has the claim again for Zac Moore and suspect he'll sit outside the lead and take beating again. DEL LIRENZA (6) was also having her first try here last time and led throughout for an effortless win. That was just her third race start and has upside. Claimer aboard again and will give a sight off the low draw. OCTRAIN (3) is coming off a run at Pakenham in tougher grade when safely held. Better than that though and is drawn to stalk a strong pace. Could be finishing on hard. BRING THE THUNDER (2) went to the paddock a winner and returns after a long break. Fitter for two jump-outs and should run well. SPINHOF (7) has been thereabouts without winning and will be winding up strongly.",
